rows.title: Your Owner (Pick a Noble)
rows.titleText:
The Auction is already in motion by the time they drag you into the light. Iron bites your wrists; chain rattles with each step. Perfume and sweat mix in the heat above, where nobles lounge in shadowed boxes, sipping wine and naming prices over other people’s lives.

You are displayed, turned, measured with practiced, predatory eyes. Before the night is over, one crest will be burned into your fate.

Who buys you?

objects.title: Countess Sibylla Cyrasse
objects.text:
Sibylla doesn't buy gladiators. She has no interest in gossip or games of silken status. Her husband died years ago, lost in the Legions, and ever since she has worked hard to maintain her family's noble status.

She's undermanned and could really use a new bodyguard, if she's lucky enough to find someone on the market that has brains and not only brawn. She wants someone calm, collected and well-mannered.

objects.title: Duchess Livia Varro
objects.text:
Technically, it's Livia's husband Lucius Varro that runs their renowned ludus. But in reality, he can't even run his own household, let alone a school for gladiators.

No, it's Livia who wields the real power, overseeing the acquisition and training of all new gladiators brought into her ludus. And sometimes? She likes to play with her new purchases.

She's bold, busty and often surrounded by her courtiers, nursing a goblet of wine, her lush, jewel-laden limbs on full display.

objects.title: Lady Alesia Cosmas
objects.text:
Alesia treats the arena like a game board, and gladiators like pieces with teeth. She buys you for what you could do off the sand as much as on it; messages carried, rivals intimidated, favors earned with carefully staged victories.

Rumor has it, her family engages readily with gangs and seedy crime syndicates deep within the Third Quarter. Perhaps you'll be their latest hunk of disposable muscle.

objects.title: Heiress Novia Segune
objects.text:
Too young to be jaded, too sharp to be naive. Novia doesn’t buy slaves often, and when she does, it’s with that steady, searching look; as if she’s weighing what kind of story you could become. 

Under her crest, you might find cleaner quarters, kinder words, and the strange discomfort of someone seeing you as a person, not just property.

rows.title: Your Archetype (Body, Mind, Soul)
rows.titleText:
Before the collar and the brand, there was you. Hunger, talent, bad choices, small miracles; whatever shape your life took, it hardened you into something the Auction can sell.

You were born low in Undertown, where roofs leak, debts break teeth, and every day feels like you’re sprinting uphill with a knife between your ribs. Your childhood was an apprenticeship in surviving the Third Quarter’s cruelty.

Tonight, the nobles squint down from their velvet towers, trying to read what kind of monster or miracle you might become.

This is the bone beneath the scars. Who were you before the sand claimed you?

objects.title: The Pithound
objects.text:
"Teeth bared; you were born to bite back."

Raised on beatings and bare-knuckle scraps. You only understand two languages: pain given and pain received.

+1 Might, +1 Mobility

objects.title: The Runner
objects.text:
"Fate at your heels, swifter yet."

Alleys and rooftops were your first arena. You learned early that staying alive means always being two steps ahead.

+1 Mobility, +1 Mobility

objects.title: The Blackbrand
objects.text:
"Old fire in your veins; the world will learn to fear the warmth."

Anger was the one thing you never had to steal. Now the ludus gives it steel and a target.

+1 Might, +1 Mind

objects.title: The Cutpurse
objects.text:
"Hands like moths; light becomes a door."

You survived on quick fingers and quicker exits. In the arena, that same instinct turns dodges into opportunities.

+1 Mobility, +1 Mind

objects.title: The Enforcer
objects.text:
"Weight is your language; the weak will listen."

You broke knuckles collecting debts, and bones whenever someone was late. The pit feels like home, just louder.

+1 Might, +1 Might

objects.title: The Apprentice
objects.text:
"Ink in your blood; every thought, a weapon waiting."

You were meant for sigils and scrolls, not chains and sand. But knowledge cuts deep, and memory can be sharper than steel.

+1 Mind, +1 Mind

rows.title: Arm Yourself (Combat Style)
rows.titleText:
Steel is the only freedom you’re allowed. The ludus masters lay out the tools of your trade; blades, shields, chains, cruel inventions made to maim and kill.

Every blade, every chain, every cunning shape carries a history: victories etched into the edge, defeats worn into the grip. When you touch one, you feel the echo of every life that ended beneath it.

Choose wisely. A fighter’s style is more than technique — it is fate shaped into metal. The weapon you favor will decide how you kill… and how you die.

objects.title: Flail & blade
objects.text: The chain sings, the blade punctuates. Wild, vicious, hard to predict; harder still to defend against.

objects.title: Double gladius
objects.text: Both hands, all offense. You carve openings where saner fighters would raise a shield.

objects.title: Trident & net
objects.text: The hunter’s kit: pin, pry, and punish. You turn reach and leverage into slow, humiliating kills.

objects.title: Gladius & shield
objects.text: The classic arena silhouette. Reliable, disciplined, the style every ludus drills into its first crop of meat.

rows.title: Your Endowment (Cock Size)
rows.titleText:
In the ludus, they joke that some men fight with more than their fists. Size doesn’t win matches - but it changes who stares, who schemes, and what uses the nobles find for you off the sand.

In Cradle, even your body is a bargaining chip.

objects.title: Short & Sleek
objects.text: Easy to overlook. Most people judge you by your scars and skill rather than what’s under the loincloth.

objects.title: Normal & Balanced
objects.text: Nothing to mock, nothing to worship. You blend into the barracks gossip—until you give them something else to talk about.

objects.title: Thick & Long
objects.text: Noticeable at a glance. Certain patrons watch you more closely, gazes lingering; that attention can feel like protection… or like a collar tightening.

rows.title: Your Temperament (Personality)
rows.titleText:
They can weigh your muscles and tally your scars, but the thing they never quite measure right is the part of you that bites back. Pride, spite, charm - call it soul, call it temperament.

When the chains rattle and the crowd roars, this is what decides whether you kneel… or laugh.

objects.title: Knight
objects.text: Pride and a spine that won’t quite bend. You fight cleaner than most slaves, meant to another, brighter world.

objects.title: Cowboy
objects.text: Reckless charm and a death wish disguised as a grin. You’ll try the stupid move just to see if the gods are watching.

objects.title: Bastard
objects.text: You count favors and grudges with the same careful hand. Survival comes before honor, every single time.

rows.title: Pick an Ally
rows.titleText:
No one survives the ludus alone. In a place built on blood and wagers, even a half-trust is worth its weight in gold.

Who ends up at your side when the doors slam shut?

objects.title: Gant
objects.text: A bottomless stomach and an easy laugh. Gant knows every rumor, every shortcut to extra rations, and every way to almost get killed for a joke.

objects.title: Caius Rayner
objects.text: Stone in human shape, with eyes that have seen too many bad nights. Caius doesn’t talk much, but when he does, it’s usually to save your life.

objects.title: Khalika
objects.text: Green skin, sharp teeth, sharper instincts. Khalika has survived more matches than most ever see; she's fast and vicious, and loyal to a fault.

rows.title: Pick a Rival
rows.titleText:
Some faces in the ludus make your teeth clench the moment you see them. Maybe they want your patron, your place in the pecking order, or just the sound you make when you hit the sand.

In Cradle, some threats even follow you beyond the sands.

One way or another, you’re on a collision course.

objects.title: Stavrick
objects.text: A walking wall of scar tissue and spite. To him, you’re not a person; you’re a challenge to his place at the top of the heap. He was in the Legions before the arena, but strangled his commanding officer.

objects.title: Succubus
objects.text: You never see her in the sands, only in your sleep. But when you wake in the morning, her touch always feels real, and the bruises that she left always bloom fresh. She'll drain more than your loins.

objects.title: Ogre
objects.text: Someone is out for your blood. Less man than blunt instrument, the crowd loves ogres; simple and savage. If you meet him in the pit, it’s because someone wanted you crushed.

rows.title: Edges and Perks
rows.titleText:
Beneath the rules and the spectacle, the arena runs on quiet advantages: favors owed, secrets traded, small mercies hoarded like coin.

What tiny edge do you have that might, just might, tilt fate your way?

objects.title: Elf Friend
objects.text: Somewhere in the city, an elf who should know better is invested in your continued breathing. Their circles hear news long before the ludus does.

objects.title: Arena Veteran
objects.text: This isn’t your first collar, nor your first rodeo. You remember old layouts, old referees, and old tricks that never got written into the official rules.

objects.title: Something Worthwhile
objects.text: You have something worth fighting for outside the arena. A wife, a child. They're waiting for you. And you'll do whatever it takes to return to them.

objects.title: Owed a Favor
objects.text: That ring on your finger isn’t decoration. A noble crest, a whispered promise: one debt, to be collected when it matters most.

rows.title: Orphan by Exalted Text
rows.titleText:
This CYOA is a mini-adaptation of my adult dark fantasy interactive novel, Orphan. If you want to explore the full world — over 230,000 words, a full-fledged Gladiator route, riveting fight scenes and steamy encounters — you can play the free version here!

Play Orphan (Free): https://exaltedtext.itch.io/orphan  
Patreon (Support Exalted Text): https://patreon.com/exaltedtext

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
